# Croqtile WASM Development Workflow

This playground depends on a WASM binary (`co-web.wasm` + `co-web.js`) compiled from the C++ source in the **external** repo at `~/workspace/croqtile`. Any change to the mock interpreter, parser, codegen, or other C++ components **must** follow this workflow.

## Repository Layout

```
~/workspace/croqtile/              # C++ compiler source (EXTERNAL — do NOT commit without explicit user permission)
  tools/co-mock/                   # Mock interpreter (mock_interp.cpp, mock_memory.hpp/.cpp)
  tools/co-web/build.sh            # WASM build script (uses em++)
  build/co-mock                    # Native mock binary
  build-wasm/co-web.{js,wasm}      # Built WASM artifacts

~/workspace/croqtile-playground/   # This repo (Next.js frontend)
  public/wasm/co-web.{js,wasm}     # WASM artifacts served to browser
  public/wasm/choreo-worker.js     # Web Worker that loads WASM
  public/wasm/build-manifest.json  # Build metadata
```

## Mandatory Steps When Modifying C++ Code

### 1. Edit C++ Source

Make changes in `~/workspace/croqtile/`. Common targets:
- `tools/co-mock/mock_interp.cpp` — AST evaluation logic
- `tools/co-mock/mock_memory.hpp/.cpp` — Value types, memory model
- `lib/` — Parser, sema, codegen

### 2. Rebuild WASM

```bash
cd ~/workspace/croqtile && bash tools/co-web/build.sh
```

**Do NOT use `cmake --build` or `make co-web`** — the CMake config tries to download LLVM from an internal artifact server that is unreachable. The `build.sh` script calls `em++` directly and bypasses this.

### 3. Copy Artifacts to Playground

```bash
cp ~/workspace/croqtile/build-wasm/co-web.js  ~/workspace/croqtile-playground/public/wasm/
cp ~/workspace/croqtile/build-wasm/co-web.wasm ~/workspace/croqtile-playground/public/wasm/
```

### 4. Update build-manifest.json

Update `commit`, `built_at`, and add any new feature tags to `features`.

### 5. Verification — MANDATORY Binary Comparison Test

**Before declaring any C++ change complete, you MUST verify that the native `co-mock` binary and the WASM build produce the same results.** This is the gold standard for correctness.

#### Build native binary

The CMake incremental build fails (LLVM download). Instead, manually compile and link:

```bash
cd ~/workspace/croqtile

# Compile only changed .cpp files
g++ -std=c++17 -O2 -c tools/co-mock/mock_memory.cpp \
  -I lib -I tools/co-mock -I build -I extern/include \
  -o /tmp/mock_memory.o

g++ -std=c++17 -O2 -c tools/co-mock/mock_interp.cpp \
  -I lib -I tools/co-mock -I build -I extern/include \
  -o /tmp/mock_interp.o

# Swap .o files into build dir
cp /tmp/mock_memory.o build/tools/co-mock/CMakeFiles/co-mock.dir/mock_memory.cpp.o
cp /tmp/mock_interp.o build/tools/co-mock/CMakeFiles/co-mock.dir/mock_interp.cpp.o

# Re-link (all other .o files are unchanged)
cd build && g++ -O3 -DNDEBUG \
  lib/CMakeFiles/parse.dir/__/parser.tab.cc.o \
  lib/CMakeFiles/parse.dir/__/scanner.yy.cc.o \
  lib/CMakeFiles/core.dir/*.o \
  lib/CMakeFiles/codegen.dir/*.o \
  lib/CMakeFiles/support.dir/*.o \
  lib/CMakeFiles/pp.dir/*.o \
  tools/co-mock/CMakeFiles/co-mock.dir/*.o \
  -Wl,--whole-archive lib/Target/libtargets.a -Wl,--no-whole-archive \
  -lpthread -o co-mock-fixed
```

#### Run comparison tests

Write `.co` test files covering the change, then run both binaries:

```bash
echo '__co__ void test() { println("Hello from Croqtile!"); }' > /tmp/test.co

echo "=== OLD ===" && build/co-mock /tmp/test.co 2>&1
echo "=== NEW ===" && build/co-mock-fixed /tmp/test.co 2>&1
```

The new binary output should match expected behavior with no warnings.

## Commit Rules

- **croqtile repo**: Do NOT commit unless the user explicitly asks. It is an external dependency.
- **croqtile-playground repo**: Commit WASM artifacts + JS changes when user approves.

## Environment Quirks

- **localhost unreachable**: Dev server binds to network IP (`10.0.16.52`), not `127.0.0.1`. Use `-H 0.0.0.0` or the actual IP.
- **Chromium GPU crash**: Playwright with `chromium_headless_shell` fails (GPU process crash). Use **Firefox** for e2e tests.
- **`parallel` in WASM**: Threading requires SharedArrayBuffer + COOP/COEP headers. Local dev server may not have them — `parallel` examples may fail with `"thread constructor failed: Not supported"`. This is expected.
